underscrub
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a shrubby growth beneath the upper canopy of trees in NZ bush that may quickly self-seed as secondary growth. [often used for cattle feed.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka under-scrub
